Unzip the tar (this will create a jbox directory with all the files in it):
tar -zxpvf jbox-X.X.X.tar.gz

make a new user jbox (as root):
sudo adduser jbox

create an html directory for jbox (as jbox user):
su - jbox
mkdir ~jbox/public_html  (make sure this matches up with your UserDir directive in your httpd.conf)
chmod -R 755 ~jbox

copy the contents of the jbox directory (where the tar was extracted) into jbox's public_html dir

Set up your httpd.conf eg:

UserDir public_html
AccessFileName .htaccess

<Directory /home/jbox/public_html>
AllowOverride None
order deny,allow
deny from all
allow from localhost, 127.0.0.1
allow from swoogan, 192.168.0.10
allow from dallas, 192.168.0.20
AuthType Basic
AuthUserFile /home/jbox/public_html/.htaccess
AuthName "Swoogan's JBox"
Require user jbox
Satisfy all
</Directory>

<Directory /home/jbox/public_html/scripts>
Options ExecCGI
# To use CGI scripts:
AddHandler cgi-script .py
AllowOverride None
</Directory>

<Directory /home/jbox/public_html/scripts/*>
order deny,allow
deny from all
allow from localhost, 127.0.0.1
</Directory>

create an .htaccess file for ~jbox/public_html
htpasswd -c /home/jbox/public_html/.htaccess jbox  (and then enter a password)

restart your webserver:
/etc/rc.d/init.d/httpd restart

Then load the configuration page for Jbox (http://<server>/~jbox/configindex.html) and follow the steps in README
